Professor Bryan Sykes of Oxford says towering woman named Zana lived in Caucasus mountains in 19th Century Russia . 
  Witnesses described her as 'half human, half ape' and covered in thick auburn hair . 
  He analysed DNA of her living relatives and the remains of her son . 
  He found she was of west-African descent and lived in the Caucusus . 
  Sykes says she could be the fabled yeti  . 
 